Former mayor Dan Plato has urged parents to change the way they raise the boy child. #DStv403  CAPE TOWN - Civil action groups against gender-based violence held an all-night vigil on the Grand Parade in Cape Town. They commemorated the lives of all those who have lost their lives due to femicide, poverty, gender-based violence and the ongoing inequalities in the city. READ: Cele: GBV, femicide a priority for SAPS One of the speakers was former mayor Dan Plato. He's urged parents to change the way they raise the boy child. Civil action groups against gender-based violence have converged for an all-night vigil on the Grand Parade on Saturday. Courtesy of #DStv403